To add/remove elements:

push(...items) – añade elementos al final,
pop() – extrae un elemento del final,
shift() – extrae un elemento desde el principio,
unshift(...items) – Añade elementos al principio.
splice(pos, deleteCount, ...items) – at index deletes elements and inserts .posdeleteCountitems
slice(start, end) – creates a new array, copies elements from index till (not inclusive) into it.startend
concat(...items) – returns a new array: copies all members of the current one and adds to it. If any of is an array, then its elements are taken.itemsitems
To search among elements:
indexOf/lastIndexOf(item, pos) – look for starting from position , and return the index or if not found.itempos-1
includes(value) – returns if the array has , otherwise .truevaluefalse
find/filter(func) – filter elements through the function, return first/all values that make it return .true
findIndex is like , but returns the index instead of a value.find
To iterate over elements:
forEach(func) – calls for every element, does not return anything.func
To transform the array:
map(func) – creates a new array from results of calling for every element.func
sort(func) – sorts the array in-place, then returns it.
reverse() – reverses the array in-place, then returns it.
split/join – convert a string to array and back.
reduce/reduceRight(func, initial) – calculate a single value over the array by calling for each element and passing an intermediate result between the calls.func
Additionally:
Array.isArray(value) checks for being an array, if so returns , otherwise .valuetruefalse